  "prompt": "What is the smartest thing you've seen an animal do?",
  "response": "One of the most impressive displays of animal intelligence I've come across is the story of a gorilla named Koko. Koko was taught sign language and learned to communicate with humans using over 1,000 signs. She could understand spoken English and even combined signs to express new concepts, demonstrating a remarkable ability to learn and use language.\n\nOne particularly touching example of Koko's intelligence was when she was shown a picture of a bird and signed \"bird\" and then \"gone.\" It turned out that the bird in the picture had died, and Koko was expressing her understanding of the concept of death and her empathy for the situation.\n\nKoko's ability to learn and use language, as well as her capacity for empathy and emotional understanding, showcases the incredible intelligence that animals are capable of.",
